Intel ® Integrated Performance Primitives
USC AMRWBE codec

Overview
USC Codec description
 

Overview

The USC AMRWBE speech codec is compliant with 3GPP TS 26.290 specification for Extended Adaptive Multi-Rate - WideBand (AMR WB+) codec promoted 3rd Generation Partnership Project ( www.3gpp.org ) and has been implemented using the Intel ® Integrated Performance Primitives (Intel ® IPP) Speech Coding functions. The USC AMRWBE codec supports all modes including VAD supported by USC AMRWB codec and has extended functionality in supporting transform and bandwidth extension coding, stereo mode and audio signals sampled at higher bands: 24/32/48 kHz. USC AMRWBE codec encodes 16bit PCM signal re-sampled by using a variable sampling conversion scheme, within internal sampling frequency (ISF) in range 2800-38400 Hz. USC AMRWBE codec supports nine mono 16 KHz AMRWB compatible bitrates  6600, 8850, 12650, 14250, 15850, 18250, 19850, 23050, 23850 bps, and thirty six AMRWBE extended bitrates, namely two mono 16/24 KHz bitrates 13600, 24000 bps,  two stereo 16/24 KHz bitrates 18000, 24000 bps, eight mono 16/24/32/48 KHz bitrates 10400, 12000, 13600, 15200,  16800, 19200, 20800, 24000 bps, and twenty four stereo 16/24/32/48 KHz bitrates 12400, 12800, 14000, 14400, 15200, 16000, 16400, 17200, 18000, 18400, 19200, 20000, 20400, 21200,  22400, 23200, 24000, 25600, 26000, 26800, 28800, 29600, 30000, 32000 bps.

USC AMRWBE codec is compatible with 3GPP TS 26.273 v6.0.0 (2005-03) ANSI-C Code.

Additional information on this software as well as other Intel ® Software Development Products is available at http://developer.intel.com/software/products/ .

USC Codec description

For USC Interface description refer to USC manual. 

 

USC AMRWBE codec parameters:

  • Codec name: IPP_AMRWBE

  • Compression algorithms: Multi-Rate WideBand Algebraic Code Excited Linear Prediction  ( MRWB-ACELP ), Transform Coding (TCX) and Bandwidth Extension (BWE)

  • Linkage: USC_AMRWBE_Fxns

  • Sampling: 16bit linear 16000, 24000, 32000, 48000 Hz (8000 Hz for decoder only).

  • Frame duration and frame size:

    At the AMRWB and AMRWB character modes frame size is 20 ms. Four consequence frames are transmitting as one 80ms super frame. Frame size at these modes is sets up to 640 (by default).

    At the AMRWBE modes frame duration varies depending on the internal sampling frequency.
